        <TextBlock x:Name="Paragraph" HorizontalAlignment="Left" TextWrapping="Wrap" VerticalAlignment="Top" Margin="4,27,0,0" FontFamily="Bebas Kai" FontSize="16" Width="421"><Run Text="Variables use mathematics but we won't dive very deep into that. A variable is a placeholder for content, which can change. This can be thought of as &quot;x, r, c&quot; in math. r is the radius of a circle. "/><LineBreak/><Run/><LineBreak/><Run Text="The same goes for programming. In order to use variables in c++, we need to declare it. This allows the Operating systems to know how much memory we need for the variable, the memory address, the type of data, and will indicate what operations (+,-,*) can be performed on the data."/></TextBlock>

